<br>
 About the big bang, and what caused it...<br>
 Well, put simply, the big bang was the origin of spacetime.  You cannot try to use your intuition from a life lived entirely within spacetime in order to determine what happened 'before' when the term 'before' has no meaning outside of spacetime.  There was no 'before' because time itself did not yet exist.  This means that the big bang does not need a cause, or rather that the cause is external to our universe and thus our spacetime.  If you want to think a supernatural power did that, then you are restricted to a supernatural power that is external to this universe and can neither affect nor observe anything occuring within it... to do so would require particles to enter or leave the universe (information is particles).<br>
<br>
