<br>
<br>
The function y=(x^3)/(16-x^2) will give you a cool looking series of lines (3 of them) with vertical asymptotes at x=4 and x=-4.<br>
<br>
<br>
lim(x-&gt;4)  y=(x^3)/(16-x^2)<br>
The answer is infinite.<br>
<br>
<br>
But mathematical Infinite and theological Infinite are two different concepts. <p><center><a href="http://orderofantondwer.cjb.net" target=_new>
